body:
**What happened**:

While trying to set up a Kubernetes master with IPVS, kube-proxy fails to add IPVS services.

```
proxier.go:1907] Adding new service "default/kubernetes:https" 10.96.0.1:443/TCP                     
proxier.go:1909] Failed to add IPVS service "default/kubernetes:https": no such file or directory    
proxier.go:1195] Failed to sync service: 10.96.0.1:443/TCP, err: no such file or directory           
proxier.go:1907] Adding new service "kube-system/kube-dns:dns" 10.96.0.10:53/UDP                     
proxier.go:1909] Failed to add IPVS service "kube-system/kube-dns:dns": no such file or directory    
proxier.go:1195] Failed to sync service: 10.96.0.10:53/UDP, err: no such file or directory           
proxier.go:1907] Adding new service "kube-system/kube-dns:dns-tcp" 10.96.0.10:53/TCP                 
proxier.go:1909] Failed to add IPVS service "kube-system/kube-dns:dns-tcp": no such file or directory
proxier.go:1195] Failed to sync service: 10.96.0.10:53/TCP, err: no such file or directory
```

**What you expected to happen**:

Expected no such errors or a more detailed message letting me know what file is it trying to access/execute.

**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:

Created a single-node cluster using kubeadm on bare-metal gentoo host. After the kubelet service starts up and creates the pods for the control plane and default addons, kube-proxy experiences the errors mentioned above.

**Anything else we need to know?**:

**_kubeadm.yaml file used by kubeadm install the cluster:_**

```
---
apiVersion: kubeadm.k8s.io/v1beta2
kind: InitConfiguration
localAPIEndpoint:
  advertiseAddress: 192.168.0.2
  bindPort: 6443
---
apiVersion: kubeproxy.config.k8s.io/v1alpha1
kind: KubeProxyConfiguration
clusterCIDR: 10.244.0.0/16
ipvs:
  scheduler: sed
mode: ipvs
---
apiVersion: kubeadm.k8s.io/v1beta2
kind: ClusterConfiguration
certificatesDir: /etc/kubernetes/pki
controlPlaneEndpoint: my.domain.com:6443
clusterName: my.domain.com
kubernetesVersion: v1.18.3
networking:
  dnsDomain: cluster.local
  podSubnet: 10.244.0.0/16
  serviceSubnet: 10.96.0.0/12
```
